  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2635",
  "title": "feat(wrapWithHits): enable async init",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR enable the possibility to init the story asynchronously. It can be useful for preload some assets before adding a widget without loading it for all the stories (ex: Google Maps).\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nWe can now call `wrapWithHits` with a function of one or two arguments. One argument means that il will be synchrone, two arguments means asynchronous. The second argument is the start function.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// sync\r\nwrapWithHits(container => {\r\n  window.search.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n      container: \"#hits\"\r\n    })\r\n  );\r\n});\r\n\r\n// async\r\nwrapWithHits((container, start) => {\r\n  window.search.addWidget(\r\n    instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n      container: \"#hits\"\r\n    })\r\n  );\r\n\r\n  start();\r\n});\r\n```",
